.TH "suspend_nvs_register" 9 "suspend_nvs_register" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
suspend_nvs_register \- register platform NVS memory region to save @start - physical address of the region @size - size of the region
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" suspend_nvs_register
.BI "(unsigned long start "  ","
.BI "unsigned long size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "start" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "size" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

The NVS region need not be page-aligned (both ends) and we arrange
things so that the data from page-aligned addresses in this region will
be copied into separate RAM pages.
